  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Typically, it involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Merging illicit funds with legitimate money\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most anti-money laundering laws prohibit deliberately disguising the origins of criminal proceeds.",
